Context
The CCS project (/Users/benkahan/Documents/kings-dharma/ccs) implements a knowledge graph with spherical coordinate positioning for nodes. The developer owns the concept of sphereQL but not CCS IP, so this is a clean-room implementation of a production-grade Rust library that provides domain-agnostic spherical coordinate operations as an additive layer to GraphQL.
The goal: any Rust developer can map their data to spherical coordinates and query it spatially through GraphQL, regardless of domain (geospatial, knowledge graphs, game worlds, astronomy, network topology).
