Layer 2: sphereql-index (Spatial Indexing & Queries)
Core Trait
rustpub trait SpatialItem: Clone + Send + Sync {
    type Id: Eq + Hash + Clone + Send + Sync;
    fn id(&self) -> &Self::Id;
    fn position(&self) -> &SphericalPoint;
}
Index Types

ShellIndex<T> -- radial shell bucketing with configurable boundaries (builder pattern)
SectorIndex<T> -- angular sector grid (theta x phi divisions)
SpatialIndex<T> -- composite of shell + sector for multi-dimensional pruning
CachedIndex<T> -- wraps SpatialIndex with LRU cache + generation counter for auto-invalidation

Queries

query_cone(cone, limit) -- find items within angular cone
query_shell(shell) -- find items in radius range
query_band(band) -- find items in phi range
query_region(region) -- compound region queries
nearest(point, k) -- k-nearest neighbors
within_distance(point, max_dist) -- all items within angular distance

Cache (improvement over CCS)
CCS: no eviction, full rebuild. sphereQL: LRU with configurable capacity, generation-counter invalidation on insert/remove/update.

Layer 3: sphereql-layout (Layout Engine)
Key Traits
rustpub trait DimensionMapper: Send + Sync {
    type Item;
    fn map(&self, item: &Self::Item) -> SphericalPoint;
}

pub trait LayoutStrategy<T>: Send + Sync {
    fn layout(&self, items: &[T], mapper: &dyn DimensionMapper<Item = T>) -> LayoutResult<T>;
}
This generalizes CCS's SphericalDimensionWeights (6 hardcoded domain-specific weights) into a user-defined mapping function.
Built-in Strategies

UniformLayout -- Fibonacci spiral distribution for max separation
ClusteredLayout -- groups similar items into angular sectors (analogous to CCS CONFIDENCE_CLUSTERING / SEMANTIC_MERIDIAN_BASED)
ForceDirectedLayout -- repulsive/attractive forces on sphere surface (analogous to CCS HYBRID_OPTIMIZATION)

Incremental Updates
ManagedLayout<T> tracks dirty items, supports add/remove/mark_dirty/reflow_incremental.
Quality Metrics
LayoutQuality { dispersion_score, overlap_score, silhouette_score }

Layer 4: sphereql-graphql (GraphQL Integration)
GraphQL Schema Additions
graphqltype SphericalPoint { r, theta, phi, thetaDegrees, phiDegrees, cartesian }

type Query {
  withinCone(center: SphericalCoordinateInput!, halfAngle: Float!, limit: Int): SpatialQueryResult!
  withinShell(rMin: Float!, rMax: Float!, limit: Int): SpatialQueryResult!
  withinBand(phiMin: Float!, phiMax: Float!, limit: Int): SpatialQueryResult!
  withinRegion(region: SphericalRegionInput!, limit: Int): SpatialQueryResult!
  nearestTo(point: SphericalCoordinateInput!, k: Int!, maxDistance: Float): [NearestResult!]!
  distanceBetween(a: SphericalCoordinateInput!, b: SphericalCoordinateInput!, metric: DistanceMetric): Float!
}

directive @sphericalFilter(withinCone: ConeInput, withinShell: ShellInput, ...) on FIELD_DEFINITION

type Subscription {
  itemEnteredRegion(region: SphericalRegionInput!): SpatialEvent!
  itemLeftRegion(region: SphericalRegionInput!): SpatialEvent!
}
Rust Integration

Uses async-graphql macros (#[Object], #[Scalar], #[Subscription])
Provides SphericalQueryRoot<T> that users merge into their schema
register_sphereql_types() helper for schema builder integration
Thread-safe via Arc<RwLock<CachedIndex<T>>>


